==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rusk
<hw>Rusk</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. <ets>rosca de
mar</ets> sea rusks, a kind of biscuit, <ets>rosca</ets> properly
meaning, a screw, spiral.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A kind of light, soft
bread made with yeast and eggs, often toasted or crisped in an oven; or,
a kind of sweetened biscuit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A kind of light, hard cake or bread, as for
stores.</def> <rj><au>Smart.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Bread or cake which has been made brown and crisp,
and afterwards grated, or pulverized in a mortar.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rusma</ent>⟦br⟧
